  "markdown": "[![Quantum Dice Logo](https://quantum-dice.com/QuantumDice_Logo_Light_Mode.svg)](https://quantum-dice.com/)\n[Technology](https://quantum-dice.com/technology)\n[Products](https://quantum-dice.com/products)\n[Resources](https://quantum-dice.com/resources)\n[Get in Touch [1]](https://quantum-dice.com/contact)[Try ORBIT\u2122 [2]](https://quantum-dice.com/)\n![ORBIT](https://quantum-dice.com/images/orbit_logo_light_background.png)\n## Why a new kind of compute?\nThe world's hardest problems, routing millions of deliveries, scheduling networks, optimising chips, training energy-based AI, are probabilistic by nature.\nDeterministic processing units (such as CPUs, GPUs, TPUs) need to emulate randomness with pseudo-random number generators, incurring latency, energy cost and scaling limits, especially as models and datasets grow.\nPurpose-built probabilistic hardware removes that bottleneck.\n![Server cabinets](https://quantum-dice.com/images/server_cabinets_light.png)\n## What is probabilistic computing?\nIn probabilistic computing, the fundamental unit is the **p-bit** : a bit that fluctuates between 0 and 1 with a controllable probability. By wiring many p-bits into a network and tuning their interactions, the system naturally explores and settles into low-energy configurations that correspond to high-quality solutions for well-known mathematical problems.\n## QD's approach\nQD's ORBIT architecture combines ultra-fast photonic p-bits with electronic control to deliver a scalable, room-temperature probabilistic computer.\nAt its core is our patented DISC protocol, which continuously monitors the quantum source of randomness to verify quality and stabilise computation. The result is precise, reproducible sampling\u2014critical for rapid convergence in probabilistic algorithms.\n### Advantages\ni.Scales in the data centre\nii.Reconfigurable and easily integratable in tech stack\niii.Orders-of-magnitude better performance & efficiency\niv.No need for sparsification or quadratisation\n## What problems does it solve?  \n| \n### Combinatorial optimisation\n | Faster, lower-energy solutions to NP-hard problems such as MAX-CUT, graph colouring, routing/scheduling, and portfolio selection.  |  \n| --- | --- |  \n| \n### Probabilistic & energy-based AI\n | Native support for MCMC and energy-based learning enables training that is difficult or inefficient on deterministic hardware.  |  \n| \n### Quantum-inspired simulation\n | Accelerates sampling-heavy simulators and lattice-based optimisation at room temperature.  |  \n[See what it can do in your domain [3]](https://quantum-dice.com/technology/applications)\n## How is QD different?\n### Photonic p-bits for speed and efficiency\nLeveraging the quantum nature of light yields extremely fast, low-energy state flips. This is ideal for large-scale probabilistic sampling.\n### Quantum-verified randomness (DISC)\nContinuous, on-device verification of entropy quality improves accuracy and reproducibility of results versus PRNG-driven approaches.\n### Deployable today\nStandard 2U form factor, Ethernet control, and no special cooling. Built for both lab pilots and data-centre integration.\n### Credible, science-backed roadmap\nWhite papers, customer presentations and competitive analyses detail performance metrics and a clear path from prototype to scaled products.\n## Get started\n[See what it can do in your domain [4]](https://quantum-dice.com/technology/applications)[See products [5]](https://quantum-dice.com/products/orbit-processors)[Talk to us [6]](https://quantum-dice.com/contact)\n![Quantum Dice Logo](https://quantum-dice.com/QuantumDice_Logo_Light_Mode.svg)\n\u00a9 2026 Quantum Dice Limited. All rights reserved.\n### Technology\n  * [Overview](https://quantum-dice.com/technology/overview)\n  * [Applications](https://quantum-dice.com/technology/applications)\n\n\n### Products\n  * [ORBIT PPU](https://quantum-dice.com/products/orbit-processors)\n  * [DISC QRNGs](https://quantum-dice.com/products/qrng)\n\n\n### Resources\n  * [All Resources](https://quantum-dice.com/resources)\n  * [Blog](https://quantum-dice.com/resources?category=Blog)\n  * [Research Papers](https://quantum-dice.com/resources?category=Research)\n  * [White Papers](https://quantum-dice.com/resources?category=White%20Papers)\n\n\n### Company\n  * [About Us](https://quantum-dice.com/about)\n  * [Contact](https://quantum-dice.com/contact)\n  * [Careers](https://quantum-dice.com/careers)\n  * [Trust Centre](https://quantum-dice.com/trust-center)\n  * [Try ORBIT](https://quantum-dice.com/)\n\n\nWe use cookies to enhance your experience. By continuing to visit this site you agree to our use of cookies. [Learn more](https://quantum-dice.com/trust-center)\nRejectAccept\n",
